title: For Sale:  Taurus Spesco 38 sp
postcontent: We have a beautiful Chrome Spesco Revolver with minor wear. According to research, the model is supposed to be near the cylinder or on the arm for the cylinder. In this case, there is a 67 on the cylinder and a 67R on the arm of the cylinder. Taurus Revolvers began coming into the United States in the late 1960s. Ten Years later, with chronic scarcity and inflated pricing on the original Smith & Wesson revolvers, in this case the Model 15, the Brazilian copies filled an important niche and earned our respect. At some point in the early 1970s, an Atlanta Importer, Spesco Corporation, earned Taurus Import Rights until International Distributors in Miami took it around 1976/1977. Here is a classic early Taurus, with 67R stamped model designation. It is the ancestor to the Taurus Falcon, later numbered model 82. Manufacturer was Forjas Taurus of Porto Alegre, Brazil, and so marked. Type is 5 screw Smith & Wesson Pre-K frame copy, traditional double and single action revolver. Barrel is 4 inch medium Pencil type, pinned into the frame, with high serrated blade front sight, and matching windage and elevation adjustable rear sight. Chambering is .38 Special, six round cylinder capacity, and note the early serrated style fluting to the cylinders and the beveled flute edges. Grips are Brazilian Goncalo, Magna service type, with cut checkering and silver Spesco medallions. We rate it as Excellent, barrel has no signs of wear and cylinder is tight and spins freely. Bore, cylinder chambers, and mechanism are all bright and clean. We do not believe this revolver has been fired much. Timing and lockup are excellent and correct on all six positions, both single and double action. This early Taurus is not only attractive and serviceable, it is eminently collectable. Replacement pricing on the nearest surviving Smith & Wesson Ancestor, the model 67, is upwards of $700.00 and more. We have this priced at 350.00 which is reasonable for this collectors piece. We might just add it to our own personal collection if we dont sell it.We can Ship to a FFL Dealer in your area if Buyer is a Non Pa Resident. Payment with authorized credit card through our store. As is No Returns or Refunds
